						               													<description>Inspired by Kyoto Shogi, Renge Shogi, designed by Michael Sandeman, is played on a 7x7 board. Each player has seven pieces, from left to right along the back rank: Silver, Pawn, Gold, King, Gold, Pawn, Silver. Whenever a piece moves (except the King), it alternately promotes and demotes:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Silver - Lance&amp;#10;Gold - Knight&amp;#10;Left Pawn - Bishop&amp;#10;Right Pawn - Rook&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As in Shogi, players may drop captured pieces on any empty space, but with either side facing up. There are no restrictions on where players may drop pieces; for example, you may mate with a pawn drop and have two pawns on the same file.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players may also drop pieces [b]from the opponent's hand[/b]. The only restriction is that you may not mate by dropping from the opponent's hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
